%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G6.1: AccECN TCP option (E0B/E1B/CEB byte
counters) write side, end-to-end. Both endpoints tcpEcnMode="accecn",
accEcnOptionEnabled=true, accEcnOptionBeaconAcks=1 (so every ACK-bearing
segment carries the option -- the simplest, fully deterministic beacon
cadence). The client sends two data chunks (200B CE-marked via the
tcptester's "ce" command, then 300B unmarked); the server's ACKs
accumulate the real received CE byte count into CEB and alternate option
kind 172/174 each time the option is actually sent, exercising G6.1's
beaconing policy and Tcp.cc's real per-codepoint byte-counting hook
against a real handshake and real data transfer, integrated the same way
G4.1/G5.1's ACE tests already exercise rcvCePkts.

E0B/E1B stay at their +1 baseline throughout this test -- a real, found-
by-building-the-test limitation of TCPScriptableTester, not a code
defect: unlike the "ce" command (which adds a fresh EcnInd tag), an
ordinary pass-through segment carries no EcnInd tag at all regardless of
what EcnReq codepoint the real IP layer would have preserved, so a
receiver never sees ECT(0)/ECT(1) here even though the sender does mark
ECT(0) on the wire (verified separately: TCPTester.cc's only EcnInd
write is its CE-command branch). E0B/E1B's wire encoding (position,
24-bit big-endian, +1 init offset) is already independently pinned byte-
exact by tcp_accecn_option_wire_1.test; this test's job is the
integration path (real state accumulation + beaconing), which CEB can
exercise just as well as E0B/E1B could.

Building this test caught a real beacon-cadence bug: writeHeaderOptions()
also runs as a header-size-only "dry run" against a throwaway header
(sendSegment()/sendData()'s "bytes + options_len <= snd_mss" budget
calc) -- for a single real data segment sent via sendData(), this dry
run fires once in sendData() and once more in sendSegment() itself,
i.e. 2 calls per 1 real segment. The first implementation incremented
the beacon counter and toggled the kind flag directly inside
writeHeaderOptions(), so a real data segment (A003 in this scenario)
silently consumed 2 beacon "ticks" and 2 kind toggles instead of 1,
desynchronizing the counter from the number of segments actually sent
and corrupting the kind sequence (observed: A003 was emitted with
kind=172 -- unchanged from A002 -- instead of the correct kind=174).
Fixed by making writeHeaderOptions()'s block pure (reads
accEcnAckCount+1/accEcnOptionNextKindIsAccEcn1 without mutating either)
and moving the actual, exactly-once mutation into sendToIP() (the real
per-segment send choke point, called once per genuine send across every
path), mirroring where G4's ACE-encode block already lives for the
identical reason.

Falsification: reverting the mutation to live inside writeHeaderOptions()
during development reproduced exactly the "A003 stuck at kind=172"
symptom quoted above, confirming this test's kind-alternation assertions
(A002=172, A003=174, A004=172, B002=172, B003=174) are what actually
pins the fix, not just option presence.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script="a3 ce"

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript="0.5 200; 1.0 300"

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"
*.*_tcp.accEcnOptionEnabled = true
*.*_tcp.accEcnOptionBeaconAcks = 1

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's connecting 3rd ACK (its first ACK-bearing real segment): kind=172 (first beacon).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.005 A002] A.1000 > B.2000: A E N ack 501 win 7504   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=172,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=0)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's data segment (its 2nd ACK-bearing real segment): kind alternates to 174.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.501 A003] A.1000 > B.2000: A E N 1:201(200) ack 501 win 7504   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=174,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=0)# marking CE
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's ACK for the CE-marked 200B chunk (its 1st ACK-bearing real segment): kind=172,
%# CEB=200 -- the real, receive-side-accumulated CE byte count (via Tcp.cc's per-codepoint hook).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.503 B002] A.1000 < B.2000: A W N ack 201 win 7504   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=172,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=200)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's 3rd ACK-bearing real segment: kind alternates back to 172.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[1.001 A004] A.1000 > B.2000: A E N 201:501(300) ack 501 win 7504   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=172,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=0)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's ACK for the unmarked 300B chunk (its 2nd ACK-bearing real segment): kind alternates
%# to 174; CEB stays 200 (unchanged -- this chunk wasn't CE-marked).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[1.003 B003] A.1000 < B.2000: A W N ack 501 win 7504   Option(s): NOP AccECN(kind=174,E0B=1,E1B=1,CEB=200)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
